b"[![](../../cdshop/cdinfo.jpg)](../../cdshop/index.htm)  \n[Sacred Texts](../../index.htm)  [Hinduism](../index.htm)  [Index](index.htm)\n[Previous](sbe48255.htm)  [Next](sbe48257.htm)\n\n* * *\n\n10\\. Fire (is produced) thence, for thus Scripture declares.\n\nIt has been stated that everything different from Brahman is the effect of\nBrahman. The doubt now arises whether the more remote effects of Brahman\noriginate, each of them, only from that substance which is their immediately\nantecedent cause or from Brahman in the form of that substance.--The decision\nis that they originate from those\n\np. 536\n\nsubstances only; for the text 'from air fire' directly states the origination\nof fire from air.\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: 11. Water from fire](sbe48257.htm)\n\n"